  .about-wrapper
    section.about
      h1 About Me
      p  I'm Matt Condit, and I'm a full-stack web developer in Somerville, Massachusetts.  I'm an avid coder, as well musician, hiker, and friend. 
      p  Starting off in a Computer Science program at Colgate University, I learned the basics of programming.  This time at Colgate allowed me to develop a great theoretical foundation for web development. 
      p  After taking summer jobs at ModusBox and Flatiron Schools, I started to realize a passion for web development.  It seemed like such a phenomenal platform for programming in a creative environment.  Even though my school didn't teach any web development, I began studying front-end design and web frameworks and soon knew that web development was for me. 
      p  Fast forward to present day and I haven't stopped learning anything I can get my hands on.  I hope this feeling doesn't stop, because it's my avid desire to learn that drives my quick development.
        
        
